arch:property.oc:show_val: Dry sieved material. This was a unit from the area of packing and possible activity floor in space 226. The unit is not completed, nevertheless it looks like it does not have big density of bones in it. This unit has mostly sheep-size bone, but there are also cattle, Equus, pig and bird bones in the unit. Fairly even body part distribution. The fragmentation is not so high. There are many diagnostic pieces. 5% of the assemblage is burned, mostly at low temperatures. Not many gnawed pieces can be observed. Very little of the bone is digested. The weathering stage is not high, bones do not seem to be trampled or rolled. The unit does not have any coherence. Although the unit did not finish yet, it looks like a rich fill with all sorts of taxa and body parts. It does not look trampled, but like low densities of middeny material accumulated somewhat slowly. NR 2005: Sample 4 >4mm flotation, 100% sorted. recorded for diagnostics and flot frags only. It is a fairly large sample of mostly tiny fragments, with some pieces up to 4 cm. Only a few small diagnostics: sheep/goat and fox. There is also a digested bird vertebra, a fish specimen, and a couple of pieces of amphibian microfauna. Scrap is mostly sheep-size. Ca. 10% burning and a little digestion. Surface condition rather worn. Looks like fill. NR 2007: Sample 2 >4mm flotation, 100% sorted. recorded for diagnostics and flot frags only. Very similar to sample 4 in size and composition. Perhaps a bit more burning and especially digestion, and a few pieces ranging up to 7-8 cm. Diagnostics mostly digested, and all sheep/goat except a dog tooth. One fish and two bird specimens. Mixed surface condition; mostly worn, a few pretty fresh.
Banu Aydinuloglu, Claire Christensen, Nerissa Russell
